overview: The user initiated a request for a code review of a sleep
  questionnaire application, specifically asking to verify that all acceptance
  criteria outlined in the  folder were met. The agent systematically
  reviewed the codebase, starting with the documentation to understand the
  requirements. It then proceeded to examine various components of the
  application, including questionnaire sections, validation logic, API routes,
  and admin features. The review confirmed that the application successfully
  implemented all core functionalities, all 15 questionnaire sections with
  appropriate conditional logic, comprehensive sleep disorder detection, and all
  required metrics. Report generation, admin features, and privacy requirements
  were also found to be in line with the specifications. The agent identified a
  few minor points for consideration, such as the specific labeling of alcohol
  intake and certain sleep disorders, but these did not detract from the overall
  positive assessment of the implementation.
